            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Hd1e108">Rubrica 4</head>
              <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De ratione morali consideratione</head>
              <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e114">
                <lb ed="#K"/>De ratione morali considerantione. Rubrica 4
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e119">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e115">Plato in menone:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e123">Quotiens
              <lb ed="#K"/>absque mente audet homo leditur: quotiens 
              <lb ed="#K"/>vero cum mente proficitur.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e135">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e135">Aristoteles ethicorum lib. i. ca. 8. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e141">Omnia
              <lb ed="#K"/>consonant rationi.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e147">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e146">Idem magnorum 
              <lb ed="#K"/>moralium li. 2 c. 3</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e149">Que fiunt absque 
              <lb ed="#K"/>ratione iudicante directiones a 
              <lb ed="#K"/>fortuna sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e152"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e159">Idem physicorum
              li. 8. c. 3</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e154">Ordinatio omnis ratio est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e160">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e172">Tullius tusculanarum questionum libro. 3</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e164" source="http://scta.info/resource/ctd99a-cuh77a-d1e164@95-112">Munus animi est ratione bene vti. 
              Sapientis animus ita semper affectus est vt 
              ratione optime vtatur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e174">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e185">Lib. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e176">Bene 
              adhibita ratio cernit quid optimum sit neglecta vero
              multis implicatur erroribus. Nihil sine 
              ratione recte fieri potest</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e186">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e199">Idem de legibus
              li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e188">Quid est non dicam in homine: sed in omni
              caelo atquem terra ratione diuinius: que cum 
              adoleuit perfecta est nominatur rite sapientia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e198">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e216">Li. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e202">Lex vera atque princeps apta ad 
              iubendum et ad vetandum ratio est recta.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e208">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e227">Idem
              de fine bonorum et malorum li. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e210">Rationis
              perfectio est virtus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e216">
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e240">Idem de natura 
               deorum li. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e218">Nihil est mente et ratione melius.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e221">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e253">Seneca epistolarum ad lucillum li. 5. e. 8</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e225">Si
              vis omnia tibi subiicere: subiice te rationi.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e231">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e265">Li. 8. e. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e235">Ratio nihil aliud est quam incorpus
              humanum pars diuini spiritus mersa. 
              Nullum bonum fine ratione est. Quicquid 
              vera ratio commendat solidum et eternum est: firmat
              animum: attollitque futurum semper in excelso.
              Uirtus non aliud quam recta ratio est: omnes 
              virtutes rationes sunt. Sequitur ratio naturam
              quid ergo est ratio: nature imitatio.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e254">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e288">18 ti. e. 2</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e256">Ratione valentius nihil est: casum 
              doloremque et iniuriam subigit. Ama rationem: huius
              te amor contra durissima armabit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e266">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e301">17
              ti. e 4. et pe.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e268">Omnia ad rationem reuocanda sunt</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e274">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e315">Idem de beneficiis li. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e278">Nihil sine 
              ratione faciendum est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e284">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e327">Lex diges. ti. de legibus. l. infrascripta.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e288">Non
              omnium que a maioribus constituta sunt 
              ratio reddi potest.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e297">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e339">Ti. ad le. acquilis. l. ita 
              vulneratus:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e299">Multa iure ciuili contra rationem 
               disputandi pro vtilitate communi recepta sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e307">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e354">Maximianus:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e311">Plus ratio quamuis ceca 
              valere solet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e317">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e366">Cassiodorus epistolarum li. i. e. 9</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e321">Fidem 
              siquidem rerum a ratione colligimus: que nunquam
              desiderantibus absconditur si suis vestigiis
              perquiratur.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
